Distribution. PALAEARCTIC: Austria *, Denmark (
Bakkendorf 1934 [as
Lymaenon tremulae
]
), Russia *, and UK ( England (
Hincks 1960 [in part, as
L. tremulae
]
), and Wales *).

Metasoma (
Fig. 314
). Petiole 0.4–0.5 × as long as wide, slightly narrower anteriorly than posteriorly. Ovipositor occupying entire or almost entire length of gaster, sometimes projecting forward beneath petiole, and exserted beyond gastral apex by at most 0.1 × own length (but sometimes just barely exserted), 2.0– 2.1 × as long as mesotibia.
